President Biden gave a speech at the OB Johnson Community Center in Hallandale Beach, Florida, where he discussed the importance of Social Security and Medicare. He praised Debbie Wasserman Schultz for her support in passing legislation related to these programs. He also highlighted the high cost of prescription drugs and the need to lower prices. The President mentioned that his administration has already provided federal grants and assistance to help Florida recover from Hurricane Ian. He criticized Republicans for their opposition to the Inflation Reduction Act and their plans to repeal it. He warned that Republicans want to cut Social Security and Medicare and mentioned a proposal by Senator Rick Scott to reauthorize these programs every five years, which could lead to their elimination. President Biden emphasized that his administration is working to reduce healthcare costs and protect seniors, and he urged the audience to be aware of the potential consequences if Republicans gain control of Congress.